pullRequest.title: Npm detectable test
pullRequest.bodyText:
Description
New version of detectable tests for npm.  In NpmLockfileParser, there are tests that recreate package.json from lockfiles.  To me, it looks like these tests seem kind of redundant to the tests now in NpmLockDetectableTest and NpmShrinkwrapDetectableTest.  I could be mistaken, but if not, then we can probably just remove those tests.

commit.message: feat(test): Created test for NpmShrinkwrapDetectable, added assertions for NpmLockDetectableTest
fix(test): Removed unnecessary test from NpmLockfileParserTest
fix(test): Replaced use of GraphCompare with graph assertions in NpmOutputParserTest

nodes.bodyText:
I'd prefer something like the following.
StringUtils.join(
            "line1",
            "line2",
            "line3"
        , System.lineSeparator()
);

That's a lot of String concatenation, its hard to read, and the "\n" might cause issues on Windows.
